context: The Nintendo Entertainment System (also abbreviated as <a0_0><b5_0>NES<b5_0/><a0_0/>) is an 8-bit home video game console that was developed and manufactured by Nintendo. It was initially released in Japan as the <a1_0><b6_0>Family Computer<b6_0/><a1_0/> (Japanese: ファミリーコンピュータ, Hepburn: Famirī Konpyūta?) (also known by the portmanteau abbreviation Famicom (ファミコン, Famikon?) and abbreviated as FC) on <a2_0><b7_0>July 15, 1983<b7_0/><a2_0/>, and was later released in North America during 1985, in Europe during <b8_0>1986<b8_0/>, and Australia in <a3_0>1987<a3_0/>.
